result.execSummary:
The defendant Regina E. Funmaker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine and costs payable as follows:  $100.00 per month, starting June 1, 2015 and on the same day thereafter, until paid in full.  Failure to pay any part of the fine and costs will result in 1 day jail for each $25.00 remaining due.

records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Sherman.  State moved to amend count 1 to State DC, abusive & otherwise DC, PTAC.  Granted.  Defendant plead no contest to the amended charge.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant stated that she understood.  Defense stipulated to a factual basis.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Find factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty as plead to.  State recommends $200. fine, plus costs.  Joint recommendation.  Defendant exercised her right to allocution.  Court ordered $200. fine, plus costs.  Total with DNA surcharge is:  $705.00.

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant did not appear.  Attorney Charles Betthauser appeared for Attorney Jon Sherman.  The parties have an agreement.  Set plea/sentencing for 5/18/15 at 10:30 am.
ADA Inlow appeared on behalf of the State.  No other appearances made.  ADA advised the court that a post-plea diversion agreement is going to be entered into.  Court set STC for 4/20/15 at 3 pm

Defendant appeared with counsel Jon Sherman.  Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Defendant entered not guilty plea and court set for pretrial 3-11-15 and status on 3-30-15 at 3:00.  Bond continued.
WSPD eligibility form.  Defendant is not eligible for SPD representation.

Defendant shall not consume any alcohol unless a physician states in writing that the defendant is alcohol dependent and complete withdrawal could endanger the defendant's health or life. In this case a doctor's excuse must be submitted to the Jackson County Clerk of Court or the Jackson County Jail within 48 hours of the bond being signed. Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, bar areas of restaurants, or where available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.   As a condition of your release, you must be available 24 hours per day, 7 days a week to submit to testing for alcohol when requested by a law enforcement officer or your probation agent. The defendant may submit to an alcohol test at the Jackson County Sheriff's Office or submit to a PBT by a law enforcement officer. Upon request, the defendant shall appear for and submit to testing within two (2) hours of the official's request. REPORT FOR BOOKING.
